<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-157-059 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 756 073</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Desktop Publishing  May 13 1991 v5 n9 p40(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Toyo color picker for Japanese inks. (Toyo Ink ManufacturingCompany Ltd. develops color picker software) (The Latest Word)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Toyo Ink Manufacturing Company Ltd. (Product development).andO;Product:   PageMaker (Desktop publishing software) (Equipment and supplies)Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Computer programs).andO;Topic:     ColorMicrocomputersComputer GraphicsSoftware PackagesJapanPrinting Industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Toyo color picker for Japanese inks Toyo Ink Manufacturing, a leadingsupplier of printing inks in Japan, has developed an electronic color pickerfor Japanese desktop computers.andP;  The software includes 1,050 digitized colorswatches, matched to Toyo's product line, for spot color printing.andP;  It alsocan work with four-color process ink combinations and can determine whether aselected color can be reproduced with process inks.andP;  Toyo hopes to licenseits software widely to desktop software producers.andM;In Japan as elsewhere, page makeup programs have usually provided a colorpalette based on the Pantone system.andP;  The Toyo product, in contrast, is keyedto inks manufactured in Japan.andM;In developing its color picker, Toyo worked closely with Aldus, which in turnbecame the first licensee for the software.andP;  The picker will appear in thenext version of PageMaker for Macintosh, due to arrive in the Japanese marketthis quarter.andP;  Toyo reports that it is negotiating with two other softwarefirms.andP;  Currently the color picker is only available for Macs, but Toyo plansto expand to other computers soon.andO;</TEXT></DOC>